<Issue id="42506" key="STL-1676" number="1676" project="10001" reporter="theahmadzadeh" assignee="amundson" creator="theahmadzadeh" type="10004" summary="Reject Transaction by TP causes loops of retry" environment="happens with sawtooth 1.1, 1.2 and 1.3." priority="2" status="10100" created="2019-09-26 10:11:32.0" updated="2020-02-24 04:57:02.0" votes="0" watches="3" workflowId="55572"> <description><! CDATA After TP returns an InvalidTransaction exception and rejects the transaction, the validator gets into a loop of keep forwarding this invalid transaction to the transaction processor; And if the invalid transaction takes more than a couple of seconds to execute, causes the processor to not respond to all subsequent transactions. And because the TP does not respond to the validator pings, the processor is removed from the validator processors list.  ></description> </Issue>
